<p>that is equal to</p>



<math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
  <mrow>
    <mi>x</mi>
    <mo>=</mo>
    <msup>
      <mo>(</mo>
      <mn>-1</mn>
      <mo>)</mo>
      <msub>
        <mi>k</mi>
        <mtext>deg</mtext>
      </msub>
    </msup>
    <mo>&#x22C5;</mo>
    <mfrac>
      <mi>k</mi>
      <mn>18</mn>
    </mfrac>
    <mi>&#x03C0;</mi>
    <mo>/</mo>
    <mn>18</mn>
    <mo>+</mo>
    <mfrac>
      <mi>&#x03C0;</mi>
      <mn>3</mn>
    </mfrac>
    <mo>&#x22C5;</mo>
    <mi>k</mi>
  </mrow>
 
</math>



<p>where x=(-1)deg k makes it real to adapt k/18 pi for the both negative and positive position.</p>



<p>***</p>



